This paper deals with the topic of intrusion detection in computer networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on using Fuzzy Rule Interpolation (FRI) and Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP) Management Information Base (MIB) parameters for detecting network abnormalities. This involves analyzing network traffic, which is a key aspect of computer networking (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques such as support vector machines and neural networks, which fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed approach, which involves statistical analysis and performance metrics, falling under the category of statistical learning (cs.SI).
